7 PART I. ESTABLISH DEVELOPMENT GRANTS FOR PRINCIPAL FELLOWS
8 PROGRAM
9 SECTION 1. Article 5C of Chapter 116 of the General Statutes reads as rewritten:
10 "Article 5C.
11 "North Carolina Principal Fellows Program.
12 …
13 "§ 116-74.44. North Carolina Principal Fellows Program established; administration.
14 (a) Established. – There is established the North Carolina Principal Fellows Program as
15 a competitive grant program for eligible entities for the purpose of elevating educators in North
16 Carolina public schools by transforming the preparation of principals across the State and
17 providing for (i) forgivable scholarship loans to the participants of those school leader
18 preparation programs. programs and (ii) grants to school leader preparation programs to develop
19 innovative ways of training principals. The Authority shall administer the North Carolina
20 Principal Fellows Program in collaboration with the Commission as set forth in this Article to
21 provide funds for the preparation and support of highly effective future school principals in North
22 Carolina.
23 …
24 (c) Administration of Forgivable Scholarship Loans. – Upon the grant recipients'
25 selection selection by grant recipients for forgivable scholarship loans of the program participants
26 for the school leader preparation programs, the Commission shall transfer the names of all
27 program participants to the Authority. The Authority shall perform all of the administrative
28 functions necessary to implement the forgivable scholarship loans to the school leader
29 preparation program participants, which functions shall include rulemaking, disseminating
30 information, acting as a liaison with participating eligible entities, implementing forgivable loan
31 agreements in the form of promissory notes, monitoring loan repayment through service and
32 cash, and performing all other functions necessary for the execution, payment, and enforcement
33 of promissory notes required under this Article.
34 …
